 figure in the contemporary American environmental movement and influenced public conservation efforts across the country. He coauthored California’s foundational laws pertaining to shoreline management and conservation: Proposition 20 and the California Coastal Act. Many of the political battles to save the coast from overdevelopment and secure public access are revealed for the first time in this study of the leader who was at once a visionary, warrior, and coastal sage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aCoastal zone managementzCalifornia. 0aConservationistszCaliforniavBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aamerican conservation.  aamerican political movements.  aamerican west.  abeach.  acalifornia coastal commission.  acalifornia.  acalifornian coast.  acoastal ecosystems.  acoastline.  aconservation.  acontemporary environmental movement.  ahabitat.  ainsightful.  alegal system.  aocean.  aoverdevelopment.  apeter douglas.  aproposition 20.  apublic coast.  apublic conservation.  arocky cliffs.  asecure public access.  ashoreline management.  athe california coastal act.  aunited states of america.  awest coast.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028308440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520958913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520958913/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY